  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This cake has no flour and no leavening apart from the air beaten into the eggs. The structure comes from the coagulation of egg proteins as the cake bakes, and the texture is looser and more tender than a standard sponge. It is also very straightforward to make: one bowl, no separating eggs, and a short bake."
          }
        ]
      },
