          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Prepare"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Heat the oven to 160°C fan. Grease a 20 cm round cake tin and line the base with baking paper."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Mix"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Beat the softened butter with the sugar until pale and fluffy, about 3 minutes with an electric mixer. Add the eggs one at a time, beating well between each addition. The mixture may look slightly curdled; it will come back together when the almonds go in. Add the lemon zest and salt, then fold in the ground almonds with a spatula until smooth."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Bake"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Pour the batter into the prepared tin and smooth the top. Bake for 32 to 35 minutes. The cake is done when the top is deep gold, the sides have pulled away from the tin, and a skewer through the centre comes out with just a few moist crumbs attached. The centre will feel slightly soft while hot; it firms as it cools. Cool in the tin for 15 minutes, then turn out onto a wire rack. Dust with icing sugar to serve."
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
